<p><span>Itâ€™s estimated that <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/facebook-statistics/#Facebook_shopping_stats" target="_blank" rel="noopener">37%</a> of Facebook users made a purchase through the platform in 2023â€”and when you consider <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/31/facebook-audience-targeting" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the scale of the Facebook audience</a>, the opportunity for ecommerce brands becomes clear. Consumers want to enjoy convenient and fast shopping experiences, and Facebook allows users to discover, view, and purchase products in a matter of clicks. </span></p>
<p>So what does this mean for digital marketers on Facebook this year?</p>
<p><span>Well, establishing a strong shopping presence on Facebook is no longer optional for ecommerce businessesâ€”itâ€™s mandatory for success. If you want to maximize sales in 2024, make sure that youâ€™re delivering a seamless customer experience on Facebook with shoppable ads, convenient ordering options, and product-led campaigns. </span></p>
