<h3>4. UGC will continue to skyrocket Facebook ads engagement</h3>
<p><span>The user-generated content (UGC) style of advertising has been dominating platforms like TikTok recently, but this content will also deliver fantastic results for Facebook advertisers in 2024. </span></p>
<p><span>User-generated content is fast becoming an invaluable asset for brands of all sizes. Rather than launching super-polished ad campaigns, many businesses are leveraging low-budget UGC assets that feel authentic and, more importantly, drive conversions.</span></p>
<p><span>Here are just a few of the benefits that UGC can provide for Facebook advertisers: </span></p>
<ul>
<li><span> </span><strong><span>You can build credibility with your audience. </span></strong><span>90% of consumers claim that <a href="https://www.nosto.com/blog/42-statistics-about-user-generated-content-you-need-to-know/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">authenticity is important</a> when deciding which brands they like, and UGC inherently feels authentic, raw, and trustworthy. </span></li>
<li><span> </span><strong><span>You can increase clicks &amp; conversions. </span></strong><span>UGC can <a href="https://getflowbox.com/blog/ecommerce-conversion-rate-ugc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">increase your CTRs</a> by up to 300%, and more high-quality clicks are fantastic news for your Facebook conversion rates. </span></li>
<li><span> </span><strong><span>You can launch cost-efficient campaigns. </span></strong><span>As the name suggests, user-generated content is created by normal users. While you may need to spend time and effort sourcing UGC assets, itâ€™s essentially free content that can deliver brilliant returns.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>If you want to drive optimal results with Facebook Ads in 2024, then youâ€™ll need to craft an effective UGC strategy. That means finding ways to harvest UGC (i.e. launching competitions, searching hashtags) and leveraging these assets in paid campaigns.Â </span></p>
