<h2>How to use these Facebook ads trends to your advantage</h2>
<p><span>Now that weâ€™ve covered the major Facebook ads trends that will impact advertisers this year, letâ€™s <a href="https://upbeatagency.com/how-to-create-facebook-ads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">explore some key tips</a> for creating high-impact, high-converting Facebook ads. </span></p>
<ol></ol>
<h3>1. Utilize short-form video to capture attention</h3>
<p><span><br />
Short-form video reigns supreme on social media, and while TikTok may be famous for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/13/video-ad-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">snappy video content</a>, Facebook audiences are equally engaged with this format.</span></p>
<p><span>Social media users are scrolling through tons of fresh content every time they log in, so attention is a precious commodity for advertisers. Long-winded video assets arenâ€™t likely to maintain audience interest, so aim to create punchy ads that land your key messages fast!</span></p>
<p><a href="https://bloggingwizard.com/facebook-video-statistics/#:~:text=72%25%20of%20people%20prefer%20short%2Dform%20video%20content%20on%20Facebook&amp;text=Consumers%20enjoy%20short%20and%20engaging,norm%20across%20social%20media%20platforms." target="_blank" rel="noopener">72%</a> of Facebook users claim to prefer short-form videos, so keep this in mind when youâ€™re producing new assets.</p>
<p><span>Grab attention quickly with bold visual hooks, focus on delivering clear and compelling product messages, and wrap things up with a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/05/best-call-to-action-phrases" target="_blank" rel="noopener">strong CTA</a>.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/facebook-ads-trends-short-form-video.jpg" alt="facebook ads trends - short form facebook video example" width="677" height="459" class="aligncenter wp-image-79157 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/facebook-ads-trends-short-form-video.jpg 677w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/facebook-ads-trends-short-form-video-480x325.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 677px, 100vw" /></p>
