<a id="short"></a></p>
<h3>2. Short-form video will reign supreme</h3>
<p>Short-form content came onto the scene with Vine, exploded in popularity with TikTok, and is now taking over multiple social media platformsâ€”Facebook included. In fact, short-form videos have now become the default content type for many social feeds, and this trend will only continue to grow in 2025.</p>
<p>Facebook actually beats TikTok when it comes to short-form video consumption among US audiences (Source: <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/facebook-statistics/#Facebook_video_stats" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hootsuite</a>). This may seem surprising, but it speaks to the rapid uptake of short-form content across different social platforms.</p>
