<p><a id="creative"></a></p>
<h3>1. Establish a clear creative direction</h3>
<p>Wondering which creative style is going to drive the best results for your brand on Facebook? The classic user-generated content-style Facebook ads produce excellent results, especially for solution-based ecommerce products or lead-generation campaigns. This type of content tends to be less polished, with fewer logos and branded elements.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/user-generated-content-facebook.png" alt="user generated content on facebook" width="600" height="676" class="size-full wp-image-68279 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/user-generated-content-facebook.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/user-generated-content-facebook-480x541.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>However, many advertisers have now adopted this approach. You may want to try out trending sounds and engaging visuals to stand out in a competitive feed. If youâ€™re in the fashion or clothing industry, consider creating more polished videos with premium-style imagery, fast motion, and strong branding.Â  Audiences expect to see clothing products showcased upfront, so make sure that youâ€™re placing your wares on center stage.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/24/design-facebook-ads-free">Here are some of the best free tools for designing Facebook ads like a pro.</a></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-ad-templates-canva-tools.png" alt="facebook ad templates in canva" width="720" height="304" class="size-full wp-image-68283 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-ad-templates-canva-tools.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-ad-templates-canva-tools-480x203.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The key is to pick one approach and stick with itâ€”thereâ€™s no time to sit on the fence! Use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/05/23/facebook-ad-examples">Facebook ad examples</a> to get ideas and inspiration for your own.<br />
<a id="advantage"></a></p>
<h3>2. Try out Advantage+ campaigns</h3>
<p>Advantage+ campaigns are an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/27/facebook-automated-rules">automated campaign type</a> where Facebook optimizes campaign settings to maximize returns. They&#8217;re essentially streamlined conversion campaigns that reduce manual inputs for advertisers and save them time. Advantage+ will also run campaigns specifically for catalog ads and app installs, and automatically optimize your creative assets.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-advantage-campaigns.png" alt="facebook advantage plus campaign example" width="720" height="361" class="size-full wp-image-68280 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-advantage-campaigns.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/facebook-advantage-campaigns-480x241.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
